    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-08-13T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-08-13T18:00:00-05:00" n="657"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d657">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">767.68119/8–1246: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in Turkey</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-08-13T19:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 13, 1946—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>577. Dept giving close study to Soviet note Aug 7 and appreciates helpful
                    comments <gloss target="#t_urtel1">urtel</gloss>s 853 Aug 10 and 856 Aug 12. In
                    view magnitude issues involved Dept has requested War and Navy comment<note
                        n="59" xml:id="d657fn59">Department’s letters dated August 13 not
                        printed.</note> and is awaiting this and outcome Secstate’s conversations
                    with Bevin in Paris (see London’s 63 Aug 13 to Ankara<note n="60"
                        xml:id="d657fn60">Sent as telegram 7418 to the Department, not
                        printed.</note>) before instructing you re US views.</p>
                <p>Sent Ankara 577, rptd Paris 4062, London 6012, and Moscow 1481.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
